<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="512" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1308,2019]" pageId="19" pageNumber="512">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1308,1334]" pageId="19" pageNumber="512">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1945" box="[420,545,1308,1334]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Aulopareia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[420,545,1308,1334]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="512">Aulopareia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with second dorsal fin I,10; anal fin I,9; pectoral fin 17–18; lateral scales 23–24; TRB 7–8; predorsal with about 14–15 cycloid scales terminating just posterior to interorbital space; three preopercular pores present; cheek and opercle naked; mental frenum fleshy but not bilobed; gill opening restricted, terminating at ventral base of pectoral fins; anterior half of body rounded, posterior half laterally compressed; live colours and patterns unknown, in preservative, pale beige with dark brown elongate oval spot commencing just anterior of dorsal insertion of opercle and terminating posterior to pectoral fin base; inner folds of branchiostegal rays dusky.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
