<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="514" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,150,500]" pageId="21" pageNumber="514">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,366,392]" pageId="21" pageNumber="514">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin 
<emphasis box="[522,612,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="514">vadosus</emphasis>
, referring to shoals or shallow water, as the intertidal is the only habitat from which it is known (soft-bottom habitats within 
<collectingCountry box="[739,821,402,428]" name="Kuwait" pageId="21" pageNumber="514">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
Bay).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,150,500]" pageId="21" pageNumber="514">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,365,438,464]" pageId="21" pageNumber="514">Comparisons.</emphasis>
This small species does not resemble any of its congeners and is distinguished by the dark oval blotch above the pectoral-fin base.
</paragraph>
